  "text": "The apparent molecular mass of Lacps1 in the native state was estimated by high performance liquid chromatography (HPLC) gel filtration, using a Bio-Sil SEC 400 column (Bio-Rad Laboratories, Hercules, CA, USA) according to Souza et al. [CITATION_1] . The molecular mass markers used were bovine myoglobin, ovalbumin and bovine γ-globulin (Sigma-Aldrich Chem. Co. Sigma-Aldrich Chem. Co., St. Louis, MO, USA).",
